# Approach
Update the memory container of ```node``` by replacing current ```node``` instance with the instance of next ```ListNode```

**NOTE:** ```*node``` returns the value of memory address where that particular *node* is stored

# Complexity
- Time complexity: $$O(1)$$

- Space complexity: $$O(1)$$

# Code
```
/**
 * Definition for singly-linked list.
 * struct ListNode {
 *     int val;
 *     ListNode *next;
 *     ListNode(int x) : val(x), next(NULL) {}
 * };
 */
class Solution {
public:
    void deleteNode(ListNode* node) {
        *node=*node->next;
    }
};
```

